@echo off\nsetlocal enabledelayedexpansion\ncolor 0A\n\nREM Dagsap App - Project Setup Wizard (Batch)\nREM Colors: 0A = Black bg, Green text\n\necho.\necho ============================================================\necho  :::  Dagsap App - Project Setup Wizard  :::\necho  :::  Bootstrap your new awesome project!  :::\necho ============================================================\necho.\n\necho.\necho ^<SETUP^> Let'^'s set up your project!\necho.\n\nREM Get App Name\nset /p APP_NAME=\"Enter your app name (e.g., MyAwesomeApp): \"\nif \"!APP_NAME!\"==\" \" set APP_NAME=MyApp\n\nREM Get Description\nset /p APP_DESC=\"Enter project description: \"\nif \"!APP_DESC!\"==\" \" set APP_DESC=A modern web application\n\nREM Confirm settings\necho.\necho [SETTINGS]\necho  Name: !APP_NAME!\necho  Description: !APP_DESC!\necho.\nset /p CONFIRM=\"Continue? (y/n): \"\nif /i not \"!CONFIRM!\"==\"y\" (\n    echo [ERROR] Setup cancelled\n    pause\n    exit /b 1\n)\n\necho.\necho [SETUP] Setting up your project...\necho.\n\nREM Update package.json files\necho [STEP] Updating package.json files...\n\nif exist \"server\\package.json\" (\n    REM Simple replace (this is basic - for production use a JSON parser)\n    powershell -Command \"(Get-Content 'server\\package.json') -replace 'dagsap-app-backend', '%APP_NAME%-backend' | Set-Content 'server\\package.json'\"\n    echo   [OK] server\\package.json updated\n)\n\nif exist \"client\\package.json\" (\n    powershell -Command \"(Get-Content 'client\\package.json') -replace 'dagsap-app-frontend', '%APP_NAME%-frontend' | Set-Content 'client\\package.json'\"\n    echo   [OK] client\\package.json updated\n)\n\nREM Create environment files\necho [STEP] Creating environment files...\n\nif exist \"server\\.env.example\" if not exist \"server\\.env\" (\n    copy \"server\\.env.example\" \"server\\.env\"\n    echo   [OK] server\\.env created from .env.example\n)\n\nif exist \"client\\.env.example\" if not exist \"client\\.env\" (\n    copy \"client\\.env.example\" \"client\\.env\"\n    echo   [OK] client\\.env created from .env.example\n)\n\nREM Install dependencies\necho.\necho [STEP] Installing dependencies...\n\nif exist \"server\\package.json\" (\n    echo   Installing backend dependencies...\n    cd server\n    call npm install\n    cd ..\n    echo   [OK] Backend dependencies installed\n)\n\nif exist \"client\\package.json\" (\n    echo   Installing frontend dependencies...\n    cd client\n    call npm install\n    cd ..\n    echo   [OK] Frontend dependencies installed\n)\n\nREM Clean up unnecessary files\necho.\necho [STEP] Cleaning up template files...\n\nREM Remove TEMPLATE_SUMMARY.md\nif exist \"TEMPLATE_SUMMARY.md\" (\n    del \"TEMPLATE_SUMMARY.md\"\n    echo   [OK] TEMPLATE_SUMMARY.md removed\n)\n\nREM Remove START_HERE.md\nif exist \"START_HERE.md\" (\n    del \"START_HERE.md\"\n    echo   [OK] START_HERE.md removed\n)\n\nREM Success message\necho.\necho ============================================================\necho :::  Setup Complete! Your project is ready!  :::\necho ============================================================\necho.\n\necho [INFO] Next Steps:\necho   1. Configure your database in server\\.env\necho   2. Run backend: cd server ^&^& npm run dev\necho   3. Run frontend: cd client ^&^& npm run dev\necho   4. Read SETUP.md for detailed instructions\necho.\necho Happy Coding!\necho.\n\npause\n